{"analytics_identifier":"OT1320","base_path":"/government/organisations/flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management-research-and-development-programme","content_id":"6fc7e0f4-1322-4469-af66-abec10c26883","description":"We’re a collaborative research and development programme between the Environment Agency, Defra, Welsh Government and Natural Resources Wales. FCERM R&D Programme is part of the Department for Environment, Food & Rural Affairs , the Environment Agency , the Welsh Government , and the Natural Resources Wales .","details":{"acronym":"FCERM R&D Programme","alternative_format_contact_email":"fcerm.evidence@environment-agency.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We’re a collaborative research and development programme between the Environment Agency, Defra, Welsh Government and Natural Resources Wales.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Flood and Coastal Erosion Risk Management Research and Development Programme\">FCERM R&amp;D Programme</abbr> is part of the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-for-environment-food-rural-affairs\">Department for Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs</a>, the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/environment-agency\">Environment Agency</a>, the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/welsh-government\">Welsh Government</a>, and the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/natural-resources-wales\">Natural Resources Wales</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":"department-for-environment-food-rural-affairs","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/65f9ae2b9316f5001164c337/s960_Sustainable_drainage_at_a_new_development_in_the_OxCam_arc.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/65f9ae2b9316f5001d64c344/s300_Sustainable_drainage_at_a_new_development_in_the_OxCam_arc.jpg"},"foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"custom","formatted_title":"Flood and Coastal Erosion Risk Management Research and Development Programme","image":{"alt_text":"Flood and Coastal Erosion Risk Management Research and Development Programme","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/65f98012aa9b760011fbda66/20240319_Logo_text.png"}},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[{"href":"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/csr/index.cgi","title":"Jobs"}],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/enabling-communities-to-maintain-local-flood-risk-defences","image":{"alt_text":"Community group maintaining a  local flood risk asset","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a9fe331f59a04b996e784f/s712_FRS22245_NS_image.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a9fe33ac93547152b9b240/s465_FRS22245_NS_image.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a9fe33ac93547152b9b241/FRS22245_NS_image.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-03-05T10:41:13.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>New guidance is available to help communities with local flood risk management.</p>\n</div>","title":"Enabling communities to maintain local flood risk defences"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"https://www.gov.uk/flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management-research-reports/estimating-the-benefits-of-natural-flood-management","image":{"alt_text":"Image credit: Ben Tonkin, Environment Agency","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/689c52be5555fb89cf3f5ee5/s712_20241007_Leaky_barriers_Image_credit_Ben_Tonkin.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/689c52be7b0b51a850e940ed/s465_20241007_Leaky_barriers_Image_credit_Ben_Tonkin.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/689c52bef0202b0e033f5ed8/20241007_Leaky_barriers_Image_credit_Ben_Tonkin.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2025-08-13T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We published a new method that provides a consistent and proportionate way to estimate the benefits of natural flood management measures. It can help to make the case for investment and prioritise NFM projects so they make the most impact.</p>\n</div>","title":"Estimating the benefits of natural flood management"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/merging-radar-outputs-to-improve-uk-rainfall-estimates","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6891eb9ff15b237bf6610967/s712_Sandwith_Pano.JPG","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6891eb9ff15b237bf6610968/s465_Sandwith_Pano.JPG","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6891eb9fdc6688ed50878454/Sandwith_Pano.JPG"},"public_updated_at":"2025-08-05T12:23:54.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>New research shows a way to improve rainfall estimates by merging outputs from different types of weather radar.</p>\n</div>","title":"Merging radar outputs to improve UK rainfall estimates"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/fcerm-research-outcomes-and-impact","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/67ef9ac3e9c76fa33048c7bb/s712_cuadrilla_20site1.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/67ef9ac3199d1cd55b48c7bd/s465_cuadrilla_20site1.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/67ef9ac3e9c76fa33048c7ba/cuadrilla_20site1.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2025-04-04T09:38:52.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Research investment is making an impact in managing flooding and coastal change.</p>\n</div>","title":"FCERM research outcomes and impact"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"https://www.gov.uk/flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management-research-reports/rapid-evidence-assessment-of-the-use-of-emulators-in-flood-risk-analysis","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/684bea3cda3d1b49e6797003/s712_climate_change_cyft4n_sea_wall_8c5501__1_.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/684bea3c72e2ed81c0797002/s465_climate_change_cyft4n_sea_wall_8c5501__1_.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/684bea3cbd35d2f88bcba2a5/climate_change_cyft4n_sea_wall_8c5501__1_.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2025-06-13T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We reviewed how emulators are used in flood risk activities. The report can support risk management authorities and others to understand the current use of emulators.</p>\n</div>","title":"Understanding emulator use"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"https://www.gov.uk/flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management-research-reports","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/689c60dd87bf475940723ee7/s712_iPad_showing_Floodline_Warnings_Direct_on_GOV.UK.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/689c60dd1c63de6de5bb124f/s465_iPad_showing_Floodline_Warnings_Direct_on_GOV.UK.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/689c60dd7b2e384441636197/iPad_showing_Floodline_Warnings_Direct_on_GOV.UK.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2025-08-13T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Use this tool to find our projects</p>\n</div>","title":"FCERM research and development projects"}],"ordered_featured_links":[{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/working-with-flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management","title":"Working with us"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management-research-reports","title":"Search for our projects "},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/flood-and-coastal-erosion-risk-management-areas-of-research-interest","title":"Areas of research interest"}],"ordered_promotional_features":[],"organisation_featuring_priority":"service","organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"live","updated_at":null,"url"